<HEADLINE> Russia, IMF Agree on Basic Issues of Loan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, July 12 (Xinhua) -- Russian Prime Minister Sergei
Kiriyenko and a delegation from the International Monetary Fund
have "agreed on all key issues" on a multi-billion-U.S.-dollar
financial bailout for Russia, the Itar-Tass news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Kiriyenko's meeting with the delegation led by John
Odling-Smee, head of the IMF department responsible for the former
Soviet Union ended later Sunday.  
</P>
