<HEADLINE> Steels Takes First Stage at Tour de France </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 12 (Xinhua) -- Tom Steels of Belgium won the final
sprint over Erik Zabel of Germany and Robbie McEwen of Australia
to capture the first stage of the Tour de France set off in Dublin
on Sunday
</P>
<P>
Steels completed the 180.5-kilometer first stage in four hours
29 minutes and 58 seconds.
</P>
<P>
English cyclist Chris Boardman, who won the 5.6-km prologue on
Saturday, kept the leader's yellow jersey.
</P>
<P>
It had been the third time in five years Boardman had captured
the prologue stage.
</P>
<P>
The 26-year-old Steels took the green jersey for the points
leader. 
</P>
</TEXT>
