<HEADLINE> S. African Deputy FM Meets PLO Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, July 12 (Xinhua) -- South African Deputy Foreign
Minister Aziz Pahad met a senior Palestinian Liberation
Organization (PLO) official on Sunday in disputed East Jerusalem,
South African Press Association (SAPA) reported.
</P>
<P>
Pahad's meeting with PLO executive committee member Faisal
Husseini took place at Orient House in the territory occupied by
Israel in 1967.
</P>
<P>
This was seen as a signal that South Africa recognized that
Palestine has a legitimate interest in the area, SAPA quoted
diplomatic sources as saying.
</P>
<P>
The meeting followed Pahad's discussions with Palestine's
Planning and International Cooperation Minister Nabil Sha'ath and
Legislative Assembly Speaker Hanan Ashrawi, who is to visit South
Africa in September.
</P>
<P>
Prior to the visit to Palestine, Pahad has gone to Jordan and
Israel during his six-day Middle East tour.
</P>
<P>
During these visits, Pahad held extensive discussions with
Israeli Prime Minister and Foreign Affairs Minister Benjamin
Netanyahu on the bilateral relationships between the two
countries and on the Middle East peace process.
</P>
<P>
Pahad is due to fly to Cairo, Egypt, for discussions with
officials of Egyptian government involved in the Middle East
Peace Process. 
</P>
</TEXT>
