<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Gustafsson Wins Record Fourth Swedish Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, July 12 (Xinhua) -- Sweden's Magnus Gustafsson
captured a record fourth Swedish Open title by winning the final
in straight set in Baastad of Sweden on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The 31-year old top seed won an undramatic victory over Andrei
Medvedev of Ukraine 6-2, 6-3 in a match that failed to bring out
the best in either player.
</P>
<P>
Gustafsson has now bettered fellow Swedes Bjorn Borg and Mats
Wilander, as well as South Africa's Eric Sturgess and American
Budge Patty, all of whom were three-time winners of the Swedish
Open.
</P>
<P>
Gustafsson, who beat compatriot and sixth seed Thomas Johansson
6-3, 4-6, 7-5 to make it to Sunday's final, previously won the
title in 1991, 1992 and 1996. 
</P>
</TEXT>
