<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-12 17:26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Syria Urges Closer Arab-European Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAMASCUS, July 12 (Xinhua) -- Syrian Foreign Minister Farouq
Al-Sharaa called for closer Arab-European cooperation Sunday,
noting that such cooperation is more urgent now than any other
time.
</P>
<P>
Al-Sharaa made the call when addressing the 16th session of the
Arab-European parliamentary dialog between the European Union (EU)
and Egypt, Algeria, Syria and Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
The three-day meeting starting Saturday focuses on partnership
talks between the EU and the four Arab countries.
</P>
<P>
Al-Sharaa said the Arab-European cooperation is the real touch
stone for peace that can end Israeli occupation of Arab lands and
ensure security and prosperity for all parties concerned.
</P>
<P>
A closer cooperation will ensure the common interests, and
strengthen the security and stability of Europe and the Arab
world, he said.
</P>
<P>
The minister called on the EU to play a bigger role in the
Mideast peace process, saying "We strongly stress today the
European role in view of the stalled peace process resulted from
Israel's anti-peace policies."
</P>
<P>
He said an effective European role will prevent the peace
process from collapsing instead of running against the efforts of
the U.S., Russia, the official mediators in the Mideast peace
process. 
</P>
</TEXT>
