<HEADLINE> Ghanaian President Starts Visit to Zimbabwe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, July 12 (Xinhua) -- Ghanaian President Jerry Rawlings
arrived here Sunday for a three-day visit to Zimbabwe.
</P>
<P>
Rawlings was met at the Harare International Airport by
Zimbabwean President Robert Mugabe, First Lady Grace and
government ministers.
</P>
<P>
During his visit, Rawlings is expected to hold talks with
Mugabe on bilateral relations and other issues.
</P>
<P>
The relationship between Ghana and Zimbabwe dated back to the
early days of pan-Africanism when former Ghanaian Head of State
Kwame Nkrumah helped the budding Zimbabwean nationalists.
</P>
<P>
Rawlings is accompanied by his wife Nana Konadu Aqdemn,
Foreign Affairs Minister James Gbeho and other government
officials.
</P>
<P>
The Ghananian delegation came to Zimbabwe from a three-day
official visit in South Africa. 
</P>
