<HEADLINE> Saudi Arabia Re-elected as Member of International </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, July 12 (Xinhua) -- Saudi Arabia was re-elected
Sunday for the fifth time as board member of the International
Association for of Lighthouse Authorities (IALA), according to
reports reaching here.
</P>
<P>
Mohammad Bin Abdelkarim Bakr, acting board chairman of the
Public Ports Institute (PPI), that represents Saudi Arabia in the
IALA board, said the re-election of his country came in
appreciation of its achievements in the fields of marine
assistance and safety guidance, Kuwait News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The IALA supervises the safety of marine navigation and
corridors.
</P>
<P>
Bakr said the Saudi ports are supplied with the most
sophisticated monitoring towers in the world in addition to
shipping guidance facilities.
</P>
<P>
The guidance facilities include seven transmission and three
reception stations to monitor the Arabian Gulf and the Red Sea and
secure the safety of sailing ships. 
</P>
