<HEADLINE> Arab League: Israeli Intransigence Can Cause </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, July 12 (Xinhua) -- The Arab League (AL) warned Sunday
that the Middle East will be dragged into instability and tension
by the current Israeli intransigent policies towards the peace
process, Egypt's Middle East News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
"If the Israeli government headed by Benjamin Netanyahu
continues to adopt unilateral steps and evade the implementation
of the signed agreements, this will certainly lead to a new wave
of instability and tension," the AL Assistant Secretary General
for Palestinian Affairs Saeed Kamal said.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the meeting of the Arab countries hosting
Palestinian communities which opened in Cairo Sunday, Kamal
especially warned of the risks of Israel's Jerusalem expansion
decision adopted on June 21.
</P>
<P>
Kamal said the recent public polls have shown that the majority
of the Palestinians do not believe that a lasting settlement,
accepted by both the Palestinians and Israelis, would be reached.
</P>
<P>
The polls also revealed an increasing support for violence
against Israelis, reflecting the frustration and despair among the
Palestinians, he added.
</P>
<P>
"The Palestinians are looking forward to a more effective role
to be played by the U.S. to force Israel to abide by the basis of
peace," Kamal said.
</P>
<P>
Officials from Egypt, Jordan, Lebanon, Syria and the AL
attended the week-long meeting to garner support for the
Palestinians in the long-running deadlock in the Mideast
peace-making.
</P>
<P>
The Palestinian-Israeli talks have been stalled for 16
months after Israel began to build a new settlement in Arab East
Jerusalem which the Palestinians want as their future capital.


12/07/98 19:39 GMT

NNNN
03:47 03:47 g # PAB
