<BODY>
<HEADLINE> France Upset Brazil to Win World Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
SAINT-DENIS, July 12 (Xinhua) -- France pulled off the biggest
upset in the last match of France'98 by beating four-time title holders
Brazil 3-0 for the World Cup title.
</P>
<P>
It is the first time ever that France win the World Cup title.
</P>
<P>
Zinedine Zidane headed home two corner kicks and Emmanuel Petit
added one to give France the most coverted title in football world.
</P>
<P>
The host team played a defensive game in the first half and were
contented with launching some counter-attacks.
</P>
<P>
Their tactics were quite effective and their ability of grasping
chances is superb.
</P>
<P>
At the 28th minute, the host team got a corner. Zidane headed
home the corner kick by Emmanuel Petit to give France a 1-0 lead.
</P>
<P>
The Brazilian team went all out for attack and that gave the French
team enough space to have their counter-attacks. In the injury time
of the first half, Zidane again headed home a corner kick by Youri
Djorkaeff to wrap up the first half 2-0 in favor of the host team.
</P>
<P>
The Brazilian team replaced Leonardo with Denilson at the
beginning of the second half.
</P>
<P>
Ronaldo began to pose greater threat to the French goal but his
shots within the penalty area were all blocked by the brave French
goal-keeper Fabien Barthez.
</P>
<P>
French defender Marcel Desailly got his second yellow card in
the game and was sent off at the 63rd minute. The Brazilian team
took the chance to dominated the match completely.
</P>
<P>
The Brazilian team substituted Cesar Sampaio with Edmundo at the
74th minutes and played the remaining time of the second half with
three forwards.
</P>
<P>
But they just could not tear off the host team's defence line
which has been tipped as the most solid one in the tournament.
</P>
<P>
The Brazilian team became more and more nervous and could not
organise effective attacks. The French team took another chance to
make it 3-0 in the injury time of the second half as Petit beat
Brazilian goal-keeper Tarrarel after a quick counter-attack. 
</P>
</TEXT>
