<HEADLINE> Beijing Reports Economic Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 13 (Xinhua) -- Beijing, the Chinese capital,
recorded a GDP of 83.9 billion yuan for the the first half of this
year, up 9.1 percent on the same period of the previous year,
according to a report issued today by the city's Statistics Bureau.
</P>
<P>
The 13.3 percent growth for the service trades provided a sound
basis for local economic development, according to the report.
</P>
<P>
The city's investment in fixed assets for the period hit 32.46
billion yuan, up 28.3 percent on the January-June period last
year. The figure was also higher than the national average for the
sector.
</P>
<P>
Beijing reported an income of 12.9 billion yuan, up 22.2 percent,
and the retail price index, an indicator for price rises in goods,
fell to end the period at 99.1 percent.
</P>
<P>
The municipal government approved the establishment of 329
overseas-funded businesses, with the total investment rising by
30.4 percent to 120 million US dollars during the first half of
last year.
</P>
<P>
Local residents' enjoyed an average increase of 9.1 percent in
wages, with disposable income growing by 6.2 percent.  
</P>
</TEXT>
