<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Renowned Artist Dies in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 13 (Xinhua) -- Shen Roujian, a renowned Chinese
painter who also served as chairman of the Shanghai Artists
Association, died from a heart attack today at the age of 79.
</P>
<P>
Shen, a native of southeast China's Fujian Province, joined the
New Fourth Army led by the Communist Party of China during the War
of Resistance Against Japan and created numerous woodcuts related
to the period.
</P>
<P>
The renowned artist served in the leadership of art circles in
Shanghai following the founding of New China in 1949 and
concentrated on artistic creations, with special emphasis on plate
printing and Chinese painting.
</P>
<P>
Shen held numerous one-man painting exhibitions and worked as a
guest professor in many countries and regions, including the
United States, France, and Japan, and Hong Kong and Taiwan
regions. Many of his paintings are currently housed in museums in
France and Japan.
</P>
<P>
Shen published at least four collections of paintings and one
book on art and painting.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
