<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Dalian Prepares For Export Commodities Fair </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DALIAN, July 13 (Xinhua) -- The northeast China port city of
Dalian is set to host the '98 Dalian Export Commodities Fair
between July 15-21.
</P>
<P>
More than 460 Chinese foreign trade companies, production
enterprises with foreign trade rights and overseas-funded
businesses from 77 cities throughout the nation have been invited
to the fair, according to the fair organizing committee.
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong Trade Development Council has organized the
participation of 24 enterprises from the special administrative
region.
</P>
<P>
The goal of the fair is to promote exports, and the event will
feature 660 exhibits from the machine-building and electrical
appliance, metals, mineral and chemical industries.
</P>
<P>
The first Dalian Export Commodities Fair held in 1987 was
China's earliest regional trade fair. The event has attracted an
increasing number of domestic and overseas business people each
year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
