<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jiang Meets Arafat in Beijing (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 13 (Xinhua) -- President Jiang Zemin reaffirmed
today that Middle East peace talks should be based on relevant UN
resolutions, and guided by the "Land for Peace" principle defined
at the Madrid peace meeting.
</P>
<P>
Jiang made the remarks today during talks with Yasser Arafat,
President of the State of Palestine, who arrived in Beijing
earlier today for a three-day official visit. Jiang also urged
Palestine and Israel to engage in the practical implementation of
all agreements.
</P>
<P>
He noted that China and Palestine have enjoyed friendly
relations for more than three decades, and both sides cherish
their friendship which has weathered the test of time despite the
great changes which have taken place in the international
arena. Maintaining frequent contacts and exchanging views on
issues of common concern will be extremely helpful, said Jiang.
</P>
<P>
China was in the first group of countries to support the just
cause of the Palestinian people, and recognize Palestine, the
Palestinian Liberation Organization (PLO) and the State of
Palestinian, said Jiang. He also reaffirmed the friendly feelings
Chinese people have for Palestinians and their support for
Palestine's struggle to restore its legitimate rights.
</P>
<P>
China is happy to note that the Palestinian National Authority
under the leadership of Arafat has engaged in unremitting efforts
and achieved satisfactory results in economic construction in the
self-rule area, according to Jiang.
</P>
<P>
The president expressed his conviction that further development
of the self-rule area and the concerted efforts of both sides with
increase personal exchanges and friendship between the two
countries will help to further consolidate cooperation in various
fields.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government and people have attached great
importance to the reconstruction and development in the
Palestinian self-rule area and have rendered relevant support,
said Jiang, adding China is fully optimistic about the further
expansion of bilateral trade, and willing to engage in joint
efforts to accelerate trade links.
</P>
<P>
Jiang expressed the belief that bilateral trade will enjoy
great prospects as the process of Palestine's self-rule deepens
and the economy continues to grow. China not only welcomes
Palestinian businesspeople to participate in commodities fairs and
seek more trade opportunities with China, but will also encourage
more strong Chinese companies to participate in industrial
construction in Palestine.
</P>
<P>
The Palestinian people will never forget China's support
which has greatly helped the State, said Arafat, adding
that Palestine is proud to see that bilateral ties have been
further strengthened in recent years. He also congratulated China
on its achievements in domestic construction and diplomacy.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
