<BODY>
<HEADLINE> National Anti-Drug Exhibition Attracts Millionth Visitor </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 13 (Xinhua) -- The national anti-drug exhibition
has attracted more than one million visitors over the past 45
days.
</P>
<P>
A morning ceremony marked the arrival of the millionth visitor
-- Sun Hu, a high school graduate from Beijing.
</P>
<P>
The Public Security Ministry sponsored the event, the largest
anti-drug exhibition held in China. The exhibition has attracted
wide-spread public attention, with a daily attendance of well
over 20,000 people.
</P>
<P>
Party and government leaders, including Jiang Zemin, Li Peng
and Zhu Rongji, have visited the exhibition.
</P>
<P>
Local schools and government institutions have actively
organized groups to attend the exhibition, which has also
attracted over 50,000 tourists.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition has also attracted donations of over 130,000
yuan (about 16,000 U.S. dollars).  
</P>
</TEXT>
