<HEADLINE> 1stlead: Palestinian Injured in East Jerusalem </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, July 13 (Xinhua) -- A bomb exploded Monday outside
the Orient House, the unofficial headquarters of Palestine
Liberation Organization in East Jerusalem, injuring a palestinian.
</P>
<P>
Quickly in response to the bomb explosion, the press office of
the Orient House issued a statement, saying the explosion against
Palestinians in East Jerusalem is "aimed at promoting violence,
shedding blood and motivating counter acts by Israeli extremists."
</P>
<P>
Strongly condemning the bomb explosion, the statement said "it
comes amidst atmospheres of continuous incitements by the right
wing of Israeli extremists and official and non-official parties
against the Orient House in particular and the Palestinian
organizations in Jerusalem in general."
</P>
<P>
The 40-year-old East Jerusalem resident suffered cuts in the
head and legs when he touched a plastic bag containing the bomb,
which was placed near a trash can some 30 meters outside the
building, Israeli police spokesman Shmuel Ben-Ruby said.
</P>
<P>
Shmuel did not give the name of the injured, but said the
Israeli police are investigating the incident. The injured has
been sent to a nearby hospital for treatment.
</P>
<P>
Orient House has been described as a future government office
of the Palestinian National Authority (PNA) in the Arab East
Jerusalem, which the Palestinians want as their future
capital. Now it is the office of the Ministry in Charge of
Jerusalem Affairs of the PNA.
</P>
<P>
Right-wing Israelis have repeatedly held protests outside the
building, calling for its closure.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli government has accused the PNA of violating the
Oslo accords by operating offices in East Jerusalem, but has
stopped short of shutting down the Orient House to avoid possible
violent confrontations.
</P>
<P>
Israel has occupied East Jerusalem since the 1967 Mideast War
and declared the whole Jerusalem as its eternal and indivisible
capital.
</P>
<P>
Under the autonomy accords, the status of Jerusalem is to be
determined in the final status talks between Israel and the PNA
which have been suspended since early 1996. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
