<DOCNO> XIE19980713.0074 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Swazi Currency to Keep Its Link with South </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, July 13 (Xinhua) -- Martin Dlamini, governor of
the Central Bank of Swaziland, has pledged to maintain the links
between the Swazi currency Emalengeni and its South African
counterpart Rand.
</P>
<P>
Swaziland had no plan to decouple the Emalengeni from the Rand
despite the latter's dramatic depreciation in recent weeks,
Dlamini was quoted by local daily Business Day Monday as saying.
</P>
<P>
Dlamini was reacting to calls from the public and political
leaders to de-link the Swazi monetary unit from the Rand in view
of the latter's declining value.
</P>
<P>
Some Swazi parliament members said the linking of Emalengeni
to the Rand has left the Swazi economy vulnerable to currency
speculators targeting the Rand.
</P>
<P>
The Swazi currency should not be an "innocent bystander"
caught up in South Africa's currency crisis, they said.
</P>
<P>
In the past few weeks, Rand has slipped from less than five to
about 6.4 against the U.S. Dollar and 10.63 against the British
Pound.
</P>
<P>
The exchange rate of Rand and Emalengeni has been one to one.
South Africa is the most important trading partner of Swaziland.
</P>
<P>
Dlamini acknowledged that the most likely effect of the Rand's
depreciation would be a rise in the price of commodities.
</P>
<P>
Swaziland imports all its petrol and most of its consumer
goods from South Africa.
</P>
<P>
However, with a cheaper Rand, Swazi products and services
would be more competitive internationally, Dlamini said.
</P>
<P>
Referring to the effect of the currency crisis on Swazi
interest rates, Dlamini said the Swazi Central Bank was
monitoring market activities in Swaziland and South Africa to
determine its interest rates.
</P>
<P>
Swaziland's central bank would strive to minimize the interest
rate differentials with South Africa so as to reduce the risk of
substantial capital outflows to South Africa, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
