<HEADLINE> Swazi Students Face Restriction in Studying in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, July 13 (Xinhua) -- The Swaziland Ministry of
Education has announced it will not grant scholarships for Swazi
students to enroll in South African universities if the courses
they want are available at the schools of higher learning in
Swaziland.
</P>
<P>
The South African Press Association Monday quoted Swazi
sources as reporting that the decision had shocked scores of
Swazi students who were due to leave this week to start their
first year of study at various South African universities.
</P>
<P>
The ruling will only affect first year students. Swazi
students doing their second year or above will continue to
receive their scholarship funds until the completion of their
courses in South Africa.
</P>
<P>
The move is said to have been prompted by the large numbers of
Swazis failing to return home after completing their studies in
South Africa, not using their skills in Swaziland, or not
repaying scholarship money to government in accordance with the
agreement they signed. 
</P>
