<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, July 13 (Xinhua) -- Indian former chief of naval
staff Admiral L. Ramdas said Monday that the BJP-led government
had committed a blunder by exploding five nuclear bombs in
mid-May.
</P>
<P>
Inaugurating a seminar on India's nuclear tests and aftermath
in Thiruvananthapuram city 2,780 km southwest of New Delhi, Ramdas
said that India should explore the possibility of involving an
internationally respected leader of Gandhi mold like Nelson
Mandela as a mediator between India and Pakistan for settlement of
bilateral issues.
</P>
<P>
Pakistan, tit-for-tat, conducted six nuclear tests on May 28
and 30 following the five nuclear tests conducted by India on May
11 and 13 this year aggravating the tense situation between the
two countries as well as in the region.
</P>
<P>
India should work with China and Pakistan to force a total ban
on all nuclear weapons in the world and resurrect former prime
minister Rajiv Gandhi formula to compel the nuclear weapon states
to destroy their weapons based on a fixed timetable, Ramdas said.
</P>
<P>
Both India and Pakistan should announce a ban on any further
development of nuclear weapons and delivery systems and sign the
Comprehensive Test Ban Treaty (CTBT), he further said. 
