The magnificent 3-0 victory of France over Brazil in the World
Cup final plunged Paris into a complete drunkenness of
celebrations and the smell of carnival was thick in the air over
the city's major spots, such as Champs-Elysee, the Bastille Square
and along the Seine River.
</P>
<P>
Police said about one million people gathered at Champs-Elysee
and 10,000 gathered at Bastille Square until early this morning.
</P>
<P>
This was one of the most emotional nights of Paris since the
end of World War II and could be the last of such in the 20th
century. 
