<HEADLINE> Arafat Granted Two More Weeks for Cabinet Reshuffle </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, July 13 (Xinhua) -- The Palestinian Legislative
Council (PLC) Monday granted Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat two
more weeks to form a new Cabinet, the PLC Information Office told
Xinhua.
</P>
<P>
At a semimonthly session held in the West Bank city of
Ramallah, PLC Speaker Abu Ala read out a letter written to the
council by Arafat, who asked for another extension of time for him
to complete the reshuffle of the Palestinian National Authority
(PNA).
</P>
<P>
The PLC agreed to accept Arafat's request and demanded that he
announce the new lineup of the cabinet by July 25.
</P>
<P>
The PNA Cabinet resigned on June 24 after the PLC threatened to
hold a no-confidence vote against it over charges of corruption
and improper allocation of the 1998 budget.
</P>
<P>
In another letter to the council on June 24, Arafat said that
he accepted the resignation of the cabinet,but the formation of a
new Cabinet would take time due to his ongoing consulations with
different political parties.
</P>
<P>
Arafat has started consultations with various opposition
parties since June 16 over the cabinet reshuffle. 
</P>
</TEXT>
