<HEADLINE> Over 11.28 Million Working Children in India: Jatia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, July 13 (Xinhua) -- Labor Minister Satyanarayan
Jatia said Monday that India has over 11.28 million working
children as per data collected in 1991 and the latest figure in
this regard would be known only after the next census in the year
2001.
</P>
<P>
Of them, nearly one million children were below the age of ten,
he told the ongoing session of the Upper House of Parliament here.
</P>
<P>
Three states of Andhra Pradesh, Uttar Pradesh and Madhya
Pradesh in the country have had the maximum working children.
Andhra Pradesh in southern India had over 1.66 million working
children while Uttar Pradesh in northern India came second with
1.41 million. Madhya Pradesh in mid-India had 1.35 million working
children.
</P>
<P>
Among the major states in the country, Kerala in the far
southwest recorded the lowest number of working children at just
34,800 while another Left-ruled state of West Bengal had 711,691
children below the age of 14 who were working, the minister said.
</P>
