<HEADLINE> Sri Lankan Troops kill 9 Tamil rebels </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, July 13 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lankan government troops
Sunday killed at least nine Tamil rebels in the North of the
country, a military spokesman said Monday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
He said that the troops in ambush observed rebels movement and
engaged, killing at least four terrorists Sunday morning at
Kumburumulla.
</P>
<P>
Subsequently troops cleared the area and recovered their dead
bodies along with two hand grenades.
</P>
<P>
During the day in southwest of Mankulam, troops sniped and
killed three Tamil rebels, the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
In another incident northwest of Kunchukkulam around 6:30 a.m.
Sunday, government troops engaged a small group of terrorists, he
said, adding that on a subsequent search in the area troops
recovered two rebel dead bodies along with three T56 weapons.
</P>
<P>
The Tamil rebels are fighting against the government for an
independent homeland for minority Tamils in the island nation's
north and east. 
