<HEADLINE> Hebei Expects Summer Grain Harvest </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, July 13 (Xinhua) -- Hebei Province, a leading
grain producer in north China, is expected to harvest 12.55
billion kg of summer grain this year, the second peak year in its
history.
</P>
<P>
A provincial agricultural official attributed the good harvest
to unified supply of seed strains, application of modern
agro-technique, improved field management and more rainfall this
year.
</P>
<P>
The province sowed wheat on 2.77 million ha of land last year,
46,700 ha more last year. 
</P>
