<HEADLINE> French Press Celebrates World Cup Victory by France </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 13 (Xinhua) -- All the major newspapers in Paris
Monday celebrated the historic victory by France in the World Cup
on Sunday, with all their front-pages carrying colored photos of
the French national soccer team carrying the Victory golden cup.
</P>
<P>
"La France Champiooooonne du Moooooonde!" said the daily
Liberation which deliberately deformed the words "championne"
and "monde" in order to emphasize the feeling of happiness.
</P>
<P>
The daily praised coach Aime Jacquet for "forging this team
into a tank of conquerors," and said that the victory of France
would increase French people's hope of tapping their chronical
problem of unemployment and escaping the monotonousness of daily
routines.
</P>
<P>
"The mystery of victory is this: in the achievement, the
champion represents all the others. His victory is a communion,"
said the daily.
</P>
<P>
The daily Le Figaro said that even before the final whistle was
blown, France had already won something more precious than the
World Cup -- a beautiful and strong image of itself.
</P>
<P>
"In this festival of nations, the French soccer team had a
secret mission, that was to give a lesson of confidence, ambition
and unity to the French people," said the paper.
</P>
<P>
It also praised the French men for showing enthusiasm and
French women for staying before the television screens to see the
matches throughout the season.
</P>
<P>
The Communist daily l'Humanite said that France has been
recognized by all this serious and brotherly band of players of
soccer of all colors from around the world.
</P>
<P>
The sports daily l'Equipe said that things would never be like
before, because France entered on Sunday the most exclusive circle
of the world, which was the club of nations that had ever won the
World Cup.
</P>
<P>
The daily Aujourd'hui said that France's victory over Brazil
was a surrealistic victory.
</P>
<P>
"The immense festival, the enormous elan, the formidable
solidarity which have united all the categories of the French
population over the past one week should not evaporate with the
great heat of the summer," said the paper. 
</P>
