<HEADLINE> Amusement Parks Witness Improved Quality of Facilities </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 13 (Xinhua) -- The quality of facilities in
China's amusement parks witnessed a remarkable improvement,
according to a recent official inspection made by the State Bureau
of Quality and Technology Supervision.
</P>
<P>
The bureau said 85 percent of the amusement facilities has met
the quality standards.
</P>
<P>
Today's China Daily reported that the inspectors checked the
quality of facilities in 20 amusement parks in nine provinces and
municipalities including the cities of Beijing, Shanghai and the
provinces of Liaoning and Shaanxi during the second quarter of
this year.
</P>
<P>
A 1996 inspection indicated that only around 42 percent of
the amusement equipment was safe.
</P>
<P>
The paper said that the latest inspection involved in 19
manufacturers of amusement equipment. Four of them did not have
the proper permits for production.
</P>
<P>
Quite a number of accidents happened in amusement parks in
recent years because of quality problems, resulting in serious
injuries and death.
</P>
<P>
This has caused a great deal of concern from the government,
which has decided to tighten controls.
</P>
<P>
The bureau urged quality supervision departments across the
country to improve inspections of amusement park facilities, stop
the production of inferior products and crack down on making and
selling of fake amusement park facilities. 
</P>
</TEXT>
