<HEADLINE> Drug Abuse Rampant Among Kuwaiti Youths </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, July 13 (Xinhua) -- Drug addicts, mostly
teenagers, have been behind many crimes in Kuwait in recent years,
the Arab Times daily reported on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The paper quoted Kuwaiti Assistant Undersecretary of the
Interior Ministry Fahd Al-Fahd as saying that families should play
an active role in fighting drug abuse.
</P>
<P>
Al-Fahd said that about 90 percent of drug use and drug-related
crimes are caused by the lack of proper family role.
</P>
<P>
"I appeal to every mother to immediately report to the Interior
Ministry's Criminal Intelligence Department if she finds any of
her children taking narcotics," he said.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that a mother is the best deterrent against her
children falling prey to drugs.
</P>
<P>
According to unofficial statistics, there are about 29,000
drug addicts in Kuwait, most of whom are young people.
</P>
<P>
A study conducted by Kuwait University on 110 addicts treated
at hospitals has found that 50 percent of them are between the age
of 15 and 19.
</P>
<P>
The drug issue has become a serious challenge to both the
Kuwaiti government and the society, with drug cases and
drug-related crimes rising alarmingly in recent years.
</P>
<P>
According to the Interior Ministry, there were 2,537 drug cases
in 1991-1997, in which 4,456 persons were arrested.
</P>
<P>
Official statistics also showed that 1,068 drug dealers had
been arrested by the end of last May, most of them were involved
in crimes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
