<HEADLINE> Johnson to Compete Only in 400m at Goodwill Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 12 (Xinhua) -- Michael Johnson of the United
States has decided to run only in the 400 meters at the Goodwill
Games starting in New York on July 19.
</P>
<P>
The Olympic hero, who chalked up a rare double win in the 200
and 400 meters at the Games in 1996, has been in a poor form this
season due to injuries.
</P>
<P>
"Unfortunately, injury problems this spring and early summer
have not allowed me to reach that optimum level of preparation for
the sprint races, " Johnson said today. "I've decided to
concentrate my efforts on one distance for the Goodwill Games, the
400 meters, and I'm excited to defend my title in that race."
</P>
<P>
Johnson, the world record holder in the 200 meters, also plans
to run a leg in the 4x400m relay. The track and field events at
the Goodwill Games will be held from July 19 to 22. 
