<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, July 13 (Xinhua) -- President of the Palestine State
Yassar Arafat stressed here Monday the need for peaceful and
negotiated settlement of the issue of Kashmir and other issues
between Pakistan and India.
</P>
<P>
Arafat was talking to the media at Chaklala Airbase during a
stopover on his way to China, according to the Associated Press of
Pakistan (APP).
</P>
<P>
Pakistani Information Minister Mushahid Hussain welcomed Arafat
and discussed matters of mutual interest with him, the APP said,
but it did not give details of the discussion.
</P>
<P>
Answering a question about growing tension in South Asia after
its nuclearization, Arafat expressed his hope that the upcoming
meeting between Pakistani Prime Minister Nawaz Sharif and his
Indian counterpart Atal Behari Vajpayee in Colombo would be
fruitful.
</P>
<P>
The two Prime Ministers are expected to hold a meeting during
the tenth summit of the South Asian Association for Regional
Cooperation scheduled for July 29 to 31 in the Sri Lankan capital.
 
</P>
