<HEADLINE> Nepalese Helicopter Crash-lands in Bangladesh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, July 13 (Xinhua) -- A Nepalese helicopter caught in a
stormy weather crash-landed in a remote hilly area in southeast
Bangladesh's Chittagong district on Sunday afternoon, media
reports here said Monday.
</P>
<P>
The four-seater chopper owned by the Nepal Civil Aviation, a
Nepalese private tourism firm, made the emergency landing at about
4:15 p.m. local time during rains and gusty wind. Neither damage
to the helicopter nor casualty were reported
</P>
<P>
The BK-117 helicopter with a two-member crew on board - a
Nepalese and a Singaporean - was on a flight to Kathmandu from
Singapore via Rangoon, Civil Aviation officials were quoted as
saying.
</P>
<P>
The helicopter flew to Chittagong as soon as the weather
cleared.
</P>
<P>
The two pilots were put up at a hotel in the city for the night
and were expected to fly to Katmandu Monday. 
</P>
