<HEADLINE> Bulgarian PM Foresees More Cooperation with China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, July 12 (Xinhua) -- Bulgaria and China could expect more
cooperation in economy and trade, Bulgarian Prime Minister Ivan
Kostov has said.
</P>
<P>
Kostov made the statement last week when he was asked about
concrete steps taken by the Bulgarian side to strengthen economic
and scientific ties between the two countries after Bulgarian
President Petar Stoyanov's China visit in May.
</P>
<P>
China is one of Bulgaria's major trade partners in Asia and
their bilateral trade volume totaled 70 million U.S. dollars last
year, Kostov told Xinhua.
</P>
<P>
During a meeting with Stoyanov, Chinese Premier Zhu Rongji
proposed building a joint electrical appliances plant in Bulgaria,
Kostov noted, adding that this suggestion would help each other
expand new markets.
</P>
<P>
Bulgaria's relations with China will occupy an important place
in the Bulgarian foreign and economic policy, Kostov said.
</P>
<P>
While China is playing an increasingly important role in world
affairs, Bulgaria is willing to cooperate closely with China in
fighting terrorism, organized crime as well as drugs and weapons
struggling, said Kostov. 
</P>
</TEXT>
