<HEADLINE> Tibetan Medical College Opens to Tourists </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 13 (Xinhua) -- China has recently opened the
College of Tibetan Medical Sciences, the only academy in the world
that studies and teaches Tibetan native therapy, to tourists from
at home and abroad.
</P>
<P>
Officials from the Tibetan Tourism Bureau told Xinhua today
that the move will enable more people to become familiar with
Tibetan traditional culture, which is being challenged by new
innovations in the electronic era.
</P>
<P>
The Tibetan medicine was developed in the 4th century B. C. and
had long been monopolized by lamaseries. It is extremely effective
in treating many chronic diseases, including cancer and apoplexy,
and is favored by the Tibetan people even today.
</P>
<P>
However, this heritage was threatened after many master
practioners were persecuted and even killed during the Cultural
Revolution (1966-76), one of the goals of which was to destroy
traditional culture. In addition, many people worried that the
ethnic tradition would become extinct because of the introduction
of Western medicine.
</P>
<P>
The college, established in 1993 to save this traditional
medicine, contains tens of thousands of rare documents written
hundreds years ago by Tibetan doctors. Tourists may now see one
of the earliest studies of embryology in the world, as well as
many ancient surgical instruments made of stone and bone.
</P>
<P>
They can also gather information on how the old masters used
gold and mercury as medical ingredients, and meet with Choru
Cerang, 70, president of the college and one of the few master
practitioners who survived the Cultural Revolution.
</P>
<P>
Local people hope that this unique tradition will spread
worldwide. So far, more than 20 countries have set up Tibetan
medicine research institutes or have used Tibetan medicines,
despite a lack of scientific explanation for its theory, which is
based largely on Buddhist doctrines. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980713.0203 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
