<HEADLINE> East China City to Attract Overseas Investment in Four Industries </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, July 13 (Xinhua) -- Jiaxing city in east China's
Zhejiang Province now encourages overseas investment in four
industries including food processing, textiles, electro-mechanics,
and electronics.
</P>
<P>
According to Jiaxing vice mayor Zhao Youliu, his city has
abundant agriculture resources, as statistics show that Jiaxing
produced 1.98 million tons of grain, 1.02 million tons of
vegetables and 72,000 tons of aquatic products in 1997.
</P>
<P>
Overseas investments will be utilized to upgrade technology in
in the textiles and electro-mechanics industries in Jiaxing in
order to gain a greater market share.
</P>
<P>
Silk, textiles, papermaking and electro-mechanics are
traditional industries in Jiaxing, with the city's silk production
accounting for twelve percent of the national total. The city also
has over 2,000 engineers and technicians. 
</P>
