<HEADLINE> U.S. Life Insurance Firm to Set Up Representative Office in Sichuan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, July 13 (Xinhua) -- The New York Life Insurance Co. of
the United States will establish a representative office in
Chengdu, capital of southwest China's Sichuan Province.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. company values the huge market in this populous
Chinese province and plans to open an office in the provincial
capital, said Michael J. Nocera, President of the New York Life
Insurance Co., during a recent visit to Sichuan Province.
</P>
<P>
According to Nocera, his company will invest 250 million
U.S. dollars to finance the construction of infrastructure in
Sichuan. New York Life has now reached an initial agreement with
the concerned local departments.
</P>
<P>
Founded in 1845, the New York Life Insurance Co. is now the
third largest enterprise of its kind in the United States with
total assets of 100 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
The company also has representative offices in Beijing,
Shanghai and Guangzhou, and has invested 160 million
U.S. dollars, mostly in China's infrastructure construction.
</P>
<P>
Sichuan Province has attracted more than 30 world-class
companies including Motorola, Chia Tai of Thailand, and 12
foreign banks.
</P>
<P>
The province has seen rapid growth in the use of overseas
investments. In the first five months of this year, its
contractual use of overseas funds exceeded 500 million
U.S. dollars, with paid-in volume amounting to 200 million
U.S. dollars, according to local sources. 
</P>
</TEXT>
