<HEADLINE> Indonesia's Mt. Merapi Spews hot Clouds six Times </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, July 13 (Xinhua) -- The Merapi volcano in Indonesia's
Central Java spewed six times hot clouds as far as three
kilometers from its peak on Sunday, an official has said.
</P>
<P>
But the volcano which erupted at 4:38 local time last Saturday
showed a sign of declining activities and thus, the volcano's
status was degraded from "danger Merapi" to "Alert Merapi,"
spokesman for the Mt. Merapi Observatory Post Sugiono said in
Magelang, Central Java, on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Sugiono asked residents living around Merapi to be on the alert
against the possibility of the volcano spewing hot clouds, reports
reaching here Monday said.
</P>
<P>
He also said the volcano's hot clouds last Saturday destroyed
pine forest and pine seedlings owned by the state forestry company
(Perhutani) on the volcano's slopes. But there have been no
reports of casualties as yet.
</P>
<P>
Merapi, 2,968-meter high, is one of the most active volcanoes
in Indonesia which has a total of 127 active volcanoes.
</P>
<P>
Merapi's last eruption was in 1994, killing 60 people. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
