<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indonesia's Mt. Merapi Spews 3m Cubic Meters of </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, July 13 (Xinhua) -- The eruption of Merapi volcano in
Central Java, Indonesia, on July 11 presumably spewed 3 million
cubic meters of volcanic materials, Antara News Agency reported on
Monday.
</P>
<P>
In an effort to know the real volume of the volcanic materials
spewed by the active volcano, an accurate calculation is needed,
the report quoted head of the agency for volcano research and
technological development DR. Ir. Mas Atje Purbawinata as saying
in Yogyakarta on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The monitoring posts reported till Sunday afternoon Merapi
spewed lava and hot clouds moving two kilometers from the peak of
the western slope.
</P>
<P>
Purbawinata said the volcano's activity is now still in the
warning status "Alert Merapi," particularly aimed at people living
in the western areas around Senowo, Lamat, Sat, Blonkeng, Bebeng
and Putih rivers.
</P>
<P>
No fatality was reported during the eruption as the hot clouds
did not hit the settlement areas.
</P>
<P>
However, the people living in the western areas of the volcano
remained on the alert against possible aftermath.
</P>
<P>
Merapi, 2,968-meter high and one of the most active volcanoes
in Indonesia, erupted last Saturday and the ash has spread as far
as 60 kilometers around.
</P>
<P>
Merapi's last eruption was in 1994, killing 60 people.
</P>
<P>
There are 127 active volcanoes in Indonesia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
