<HEADLINE> 7 Killed in Road Accident in Thailand </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
BANGKOK, July 13 (Xinhua) -- Seven people were killed and
three others seriously injured in a road accident in western
Thailand's province of Kanchanaburi Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The accident happened when a car collided head-on with a
pick-up truck which was traveling at high speed, the Bangkok Post
reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
The crash killed all five people -- one man and four women --
in the car, and two other women in the pick-up truck.
</P>
<P>
The pick-up driver and two other female passengers were badly
hurt and taken to local hospital. 
