<HEADLINE> Ronaldo Should not Have Played: Zagallo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SAINT-DENIS, France, July 12 (Xinhua) -- Brazilian coach Zagallo
said on Sunday star striker had an illness before the final and should
not have played.
</P>
<P>
"We had a very big trauma. Ronaldo should not have played the game.
He had a problem. The whole team was upset by this," Zagallo said
after Brazil lost to France 3-0 in the final.
</P>
<P>
Brazilian squad doctor Lidio Toledo revealed that Ronaldo had a
stomach upset two hours before the game.
</P>
<P>
Zagallo was apparently annoyed by a question concerning this matter
by the Brazilian media in the post-game news conference.
</P>
<P>
"He played because he played. I have the morality and personality
to come up here. I am man enough. You owe me a lot," he angrily
replied.
</P>
<P>
Ronaldo's name did not appear in a line-up hand-out before the
match but organizers later corrected the mistake, saying he had passed
a test on his ankle. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
