<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jacquet not to Forgive Critics </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SAINT-DENIS, July 12 (Xinhua) -- French coach Aime Jacquet blasted
the media for years of "betrayal" and said he would never forgive
those who had criticized him.
</P>
<P>
He said: "We were betrayed by the journalists over the years.
France now knows it has a great team with great players."
</P>
<P>
His team, regarded as long shots for the World Cup before the
tournament, beat Brazil 3-0 in Sunday's final to lift the cup for the
first time.
</P>
<P>
Asked if he would forgive his critics, Jacquet said: "I will never
forgive, never will I forgive." 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
