<BODY>
<HEADLINE> France Play Great Game: Zagallo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SAINT-DENIS, July 12 (Xinhua) -- Brazil coach Mario Zagallo said on
Sunday France played a great game and deserved the victory in the
World Cup final.
</P>
<P>
"France played a brilliant game," he said after Brazilians lost 3-0
to the hosts.
</P>
<P>
"The whole country was behind the national team. For us it will
have to be another time unfortunately," said Zagallo, whose team had
aimed for a fifth World Cup title.
</P>
<P>
"I would have liked to have given Brazil a fifth World Cup. We did
everything we could but it wasn't our night. France were the better
team." 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
