<BODY>
<HEADLINE> France's Djorkaeff Sings Praises for Coach </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 12 (Xinhua) -- Midfielder Youri Djorkaeff has sung
praises for French coach Aime Jacquet, saying he had brought
solidarity to the team.
</P>
<P>
"Aime Jacquet has been extraordinary," he said Sunday night. "We've
been together for four years working for this."
</P>
<P>
He added: "He has helped us to change mentally, physically,
tactically and technically.
</P>
<P>
"We've been telling each other all the time that we were going to
be world champions. We believed it and now we've done it."
</P>
<P>
He said part of the victory owned to the fact that several key
players are playing in major European leagues.
</P>
<P>
"The fact that a lot of us play abroad in big clubs has helped a
lot. Before people always said that the French played well but they
could never go beyond a certain level. That's all over now."
</P>
<P>
France beat Brazil 3-0 in their first ever World Cup final at the
Stade de France here. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
